<L>__{exterior car. day}
<A>__{late afternoon. they're driving on the interstate. anthony's got a copy of runner's world magazine.}
<C>__{anthony}
<D>__{here's mine right here. see?}
<A>__{anthony lifts up his foot so dignan can compare his shoe with the picture.}
<C>__{dignan}
<D>__{see if mine are in there.}
<C>__{anthony}
<P>__{(looks at dignan's shoes)}
<D>__{dignan, those aren't running shoes.}
<C>__{dignan}
<D>__{yes, they are.}
<C>__{anthony}
<D>__{look at the treads on those.}
<C>__{dignan}
<D>__{what about them?}
<C>__{anthony}
<D>__{they obviously weren't designed for racing.}
<C>__{dignan}
<D>__{well, those treads stink. you'd blow a knee out racing on those.}
<C>__{bob}
<D>__{will you guys shut up? god. it's like having two little kids in the car.}
<C>__{anthony}
<D>__{ok, dad.}
<C>__{dignan}
<D>__{really. ok, dad. but seriously, anthony. these are fast shoes.}
<C>__{anthony}
<D>__{you've never had a pair of fast shoes in your life, dignan.}
<P>__{(to bob)}
<D>__{in fifth grade dignan used to wear cowboy boots for p.e.}
<C>__{dignan}
<D>__{that's real cool, anthony. yeah, i wore boots. my parents wouldn't buy me any $200 running shoes like yours. i wasn't spoiled.}
